                    	<note xml:id="n_dating" type="dating">
                    	    
<p xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">The letter was written when Van Gogh was allowed to leave the hospital for a few hours and went to the Yellow House (<ref target="#l-7">ll. 7-11</ref>, <ref target="#l-40">40-42</ref>). This was on Friday, 4 January 1889, as evidenced by a letter Joseph Roulin sent on this day to Theo (FR b1068).</p>
                    	</note>
                    
                    
                    
                    	<note xml:id="n_remarks" type="remarks">
                    	    
                                    
                                    
<p xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">Previously the two letters, the one to Theo and the one to Gauguin, were included under one number. Here we have separated them. For the second letter, see <ref target="let730.xml">730</ref>.</p>
                                
